{"title_page": "Anupamaa", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian television series}}{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Anupamaa the fail the faltu\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Drama]]\n| creator                  = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| story                    = \n| screenplay               = \n| director                 = Rajan Shahi\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = [[Rupali Ganguly]]<br>[[Sudhanshu Pandey]]\n| opentheme                = \n| country                  = India\n| language                 = Hindi\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = Rajan Shahi\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = Multi-camera\n| runtime                  = 20\u201325 minutes\n| network                  = [[Star Plus]]\n| picture_format           = [[576i]] <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|df=yes|||}}\n| last_aired               = \n| website                  = \n| website_title            = \n| list_episodes            = \n| image_alt                = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| production_website       = https://www.directorskut.co.in\n| production_website_title = Director's Kut Production\n| company                  = [[Director's Kut Productions]]\n}}\n\n'''''Anupamaa''''' is an Indian drama television series that would premiere on [[Star Plus]]. It is a remake of [[Star Jalsha]]'s [[Bengali language|Bengali series]] ''[[Sreemoyee]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rupali-ganguly-sudhanshu-pandey-starrer-anupamaa-is-a-remake-of-a-popular-benagli-show-sreemoyee/articleshow/74323173.cms|title=Rupali Ganguly- Sudhanshu Pandey starrer Anupamaa is a remake of a popular Bengali show 'Sreemoyee'|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Produced by Rajan Shahi under [[Director's Kut Productions]], it stars [[Rupali Ganguly]] and [[Sudhanshu Pandey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rupali-ganguly-back-on-a-fiction-show-after-seven-years/articleshow/74241593.cms|title=Rupali Ganguly back on a fiction show after seven years|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nHomemaker Anupamaa has dedicated her life for her family but she doesn't get valued for it. She is always taken for granted. \n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Rupali Ganguly]] as Anupamaa: Vanraj's wife; Paritosh, Samar and Pakhi's mother\n* [[Sudhanshu Pandey]] as Vanraj: Anupamaa's husband; Paritosh, Samar and Pakhi's father\n* [[Paras Kalnawat]] as Samar: Anupamaa and Vanraj's eldest son; Paritosh and Pakhi's brother\n\n===Recurring===\n* Aashish Mehrotra as Paritosh: Anupamaa and Vanraj's son; Samar and Pakhi's brother\n* Muskan Bamne as Pakhi: Anupamaa and Vanraj's daughter; Paritosh and Samar's sister\n* [[Additi Gupta]] as Kavya: Vanraj's colleague\n* [[Jasveer Kaur]]\n* Ekta Saraiya as Vanraj's sister\n* Arvind Vaidya as Vanraj's father\n* Alpana Buch as Vanraj's mother\n\n==Production ==\nRajan Shahi, the producer of the Marathi remake of ''[[Sreemoyee]]'' titled ''[[Aai Kuthe Kay Karte]]'' on [[Star Pravah]] planned to produce its Hindi remake ''Anupamaa'' stating, \"This interesting concept around a mother\u2019s journey has been so inspirational that Star wants to bring it in Hindi too.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/television/news/yeh-rishta-kya-kehlata-hai-maker-rajan-shahi-remake-marathi-show-aai-kuthe-kay-karte-star-plus/2020/02/06|title=Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai maker Rajan Shahi to remake his Marathi show Aai Kuthe Kay Karte for Star Plus|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nEarlier locked to be premiered on 16 March 2020, it was indefinitely postponed amid [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coronavirus-tv-channels-to-rely-on-episode-banks-alternative-content-amid-production-halt/1763290|title=Coronavirus: TV channels to rely on episode banks, alternative content amid production halt|last=|first=|date=|website=Outlook India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Star Plus television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:2020s Indian television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian television series}}{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Anupamaa\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Drama]]\n| creator                  = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| story                    = \n| screenplay               = \n| director                 = Rajan Shahi\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = [[Rupali Ganguly]]<br>[[Sudhanshu Pandey]]\n| opentheme                = \n| country                  = India\n| language                 = Hindi\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = Rajan Shahi\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = Multi-camera\n| runtime                  = 20\u201325 minutes\n| network                  = [[Star Plus]]\n| picture_format           = [[576i]] <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|df=yes|||}}\n| last_aired               = \n| website                  = \n| website_title            = \n| list_episodes            = \n| image_alt                = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| production_website       = https://www.directorskut.co.in\n| production_website_title = Director's Kut Production\n| company                  = [[Director's Kut Productions]]\n}}\n\n'''''Anupamaa''''' is an Indian drama television series that would premiere on [[Star Plus]]. It is a remake of [[Star Jalsha]]'s [[Bengali language|Bengali series]] ''[[Sreemoyee]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rupali-ganguly-sudhanshu-pandey-starrer-anupamaa-is-a-remake-of-a-popular-benagli-show-sreemoyee/articleshow/74323173.cms|title=Rupali Ganguly- Sudhanshu Pandey starrer Anupamaa is a remake of a popular Bengali show 'Sreemoyee'|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Produced by Rajan Shahi under [[Director's Kut Productions]], it stars [[Rupali Ganguly]] and [[Sudhanshu Pandey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rupali-ganguly-back-on-a-fiction-show-after-seven-years/articleshow/74241593.cms|title=Rupali Ganguly back on a fiction show after seven years|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nHomemaker Anupamaa has dedicated her life for her family but she doesn't get valued for it. She is always taken for granted. \n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Rupali Ganguly]] as Anupamaa: Vanraj's wife; Paritosh, Samar and Pakhi's mother\n* [[Sudhanshu Pandey]] as Vanraj: Anupamaa's husband; Paritosh, Samar and Pakhi's father\n* [[Paras Kalnawat]] as Samar: Anupamaa and Vanraj's eldest son; Paritosh and Pakhi's brother\n\n===Recurring===\n* Aashish Mehrotra as Paritosh: Anupamaa and Vanraj's son; Samar and Pakhi's brother\n* Muskan Bamne as Pakhi: Anupamaa and Vanraj's daughter; Paritosh and Samar's sister\n* [[Additi Gupta]] as Kavya: Vanraj's colleague\n* [[Jasveer Kaur]]\n* Ekta Saraiya as Vanraj's sister\n* Arvind Vaidya as Vanraj's father\n* Alpana Buch as Vanraj's mother\n\n==Production ==\nRajan Shahi, the producer of the Marathi remake of ''[[Sreemoyee]]'' titled ''[[Aai Kuthe Kay Karte]]'' on [[Star Pravah]] planned to produce its Hindi remake ''Anupamaa'' stating, \"This interesting concept around a mother\u2019s journey has been so inspirational that Star wants to bring it in Hindi too.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/television/news/yeh-rishta-kya-kehlata-hai-maker-rajan-shahi-remake-marathi-show-aai-kuthe-kay-karte-star-plus/2020/02/06|title=Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai maker Rajan Shahi to remake his Marathi show Aai Kuthe Kay Karte for Star Plus|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nEarlier locked to be premiered on 16 March 2020, it was indefinitely postponed amid [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coronavirus-tv-channels-to-rely-on-episode-banks-alternative-content-amid-production-halt/1763290|title=Coronavirus: TV channels to rely on episode banks, alternative content amid production halt|last=|first=|date=|website=Outlook India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Star Plus television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:2020s Indian television series]]\n", "name_user": "123.253.38.26", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anupamaa"}
