{"title_page": "Lucia (film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lucia<br />\u0cb2\u0cc2\u0cb8\u0cbf\u0caf\n| image          = Lucia kannada film poster1.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]]\n| producer       = Audience films<br />Home Talkies\n| writer         = Pawan Kumar\n| screenplay     = Pawan Kumar\n| starring       = [[Sathish Ninasam]]<br />[[Sruthi Hariharan]]<br />[[Achyuth Kumar]]<br />[[Rishab Shetty]]\n| music          = [[Poornachandra Tejaswi (composer)|Poornachandra Tejaswi]]<br />'''Background music:'''<br />Poornachandra Tejaswi<br />Monish Kumar M. K.<br />[[Santhosh Narayanan]]\n| cinematography = [[Siddhartha Nuni]]\n| studio         = Audience films\n| distributor    = Home Talkies\n| editing        = Sanath\u2013Suresh<br />Pawan Kumar\n| released       = {{Film date|2013|07|20|[[London Film Festival]]|2013|9|6|India|df=y}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref name=\"th1\" />\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|3.6|c}}\n}}\n\n'''''Lucia''''' is a 2013 Indian [[Kannada]]-language [[romantic]] [[psychological thriller]] film written, co-edited and directed by [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Crowd-funding show gains pace with Kannada movie Lucia, over 100 people invest through Facebook & blog |url= http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2013-04-13/news/38511296_1_kannada-film-industry-lifeu-ishtene-first-kannada-movie |newspaper= The Economic Times |date= 13 April 2013}}</ref> It stars [[Sathish Ninasam]] and [[Sruthi Hariharan]].''<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-12/news-and-interviews/35049155_1_double-role-kannada-flick Sruthi gets busy \u2013 The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>''\n\nThe film's plot is about Nikki, an usher in theatre who has insomnia. After consuming a special pill, he gets entangled in a different kind of dream. ''Lucia'' was the first Kannada film to be [[crowdfunded]] by the people which created a trend. The film's soundtrack was composed by Poornachandra Tejaswi and cinematography was handled by [[Siddhartha Nuni]].\n\n''Lucia'' premiered at the [[London Indian Film Festival]] on 20 July 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title= Lucia to premiere at LIFF |url= http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Lucia-to-premiere-at-LIFF/2013/07/02/article1662455.ece |newspaper= The Indian Express |date= 2 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Indian Film Festival 2013&nbsp;\u2013 London |url= http://www.britishsouthindians.co.uk/indian-film-festival-2013-london/ |publisher= britishsouthindians}}</ref> It won the Best Film Audience Choice award at the festival.<ref>{{cite news |title= Crowd-funded 'Lucia' wins smash hit 4th edition of LIFF |url= http://www.londonindianfilmfestival.co.uk/cgi-bin/template.pl?t=npd&ID=130 |publisher= London Indian Film Festival |access-date= 15 August 2013 |archive-url= https://archive.is/20130815032638/http://www.londonindianfilmfestival.co.uk/cgi-bin/template.pl?t=npd&ID=130 |archive-date= 15 August 2013 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\nIt was also among the films shortlisted by the FFI to become India's submission for Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film for the year 2013. The film was also remade in Tamil as ''[[Enakkul Oruvan (2015 film)|Enakkul Oruvan]]'' in 2015.\n\n==Plot==\n{{tone|section|date=August 2015}}\nThe plot is non-linear, and the end scene of the film shows the real beginning of the story.<ref name=fiction>{{cite news|title=Stranger than fiction|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/stranger-than-fiction/article5149845.ece|accessdate=4 November 2013|newspaper=TheHindu|date=20 September 2013}}</ref> There are two main roles, one that is played out in the dream, and the other one in reality, called respectively Nikhil and Nikki.<ref name=fiction/> The plot starts with the protagonist being in a state of coma and continuing only on life support. The film, from the beginning, tells two stories of the same person, one in colour and the other in black and white.<ref name=sarit>{{cite news|title=Sarit Ray's review: Lucia|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Sarit-Ray-s-review-Lucia/Article1-1119075.aspx|accessdate=4 November 2013|newspaper=The Hindustan Times|date=8 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nSanjay, a detective from the Mumbai police Crime Branch starts investigating the incident that caused the protagonist's ([[Sathish Ninasam]]) current state. While Sanjay is going through the protagonist's belongings he stumbles upon some scribbled notes and a mysterious pill. Meanwhile, the police capture two suspects and interrogate them.\n\nThe story starts with Nikki in a village near Mandya, working as an usher/\"torch-shiner\" in a Bengaluru movie theatre owned by Shankranna (Achyuth Kumar). Nikki has insomnia and yearns for a companion. On one of his sleepless nights Nikki is contacted by a drug dealer who gives him Lucia pills as a solution to his sleeping problems. This drug is said to have the capacity to help one dream the life they want, but has the side-effect that upon discontinuation the same dreams turn into nightmares.\n\nWith the help of the Lucia pills, Nikki starts seeing himself as being a successful actor called Nikhil surrounded by people he knows in the real world. Film actor Nikhil's life is depicted in black-and-white. Shankranna, the owner of the theater where Nikki works, had starred in a film in his youth funded by the leader of some goons who now want Shankranna to sign off his theatre for his debt. More events from the dream are followed by similar events in reality as Nikki falls in love with Shwetha ([[Sruthi Hariharan]]) who is a model in the dream and a waitress in reality.\n\nIn the dream, Nikhil and Shwetha hit it off easily at the beginning but later friction arises when Nikhil expresses his discontent about Shwetha working in the film industry. Meanwhile, in reality, Nikki struggles to win Shwetha's heart, who rejects him first due to his low salary but later falls for his humble character. Shwetha's attempts to get Nikki educated and lead him to find a better paying job turns out to be futile and also result in the death of Shankranna in the hands of goons. Frustrated, Nikki chooses to leave Shwetha and continue to work in the theatre, despite the threats. Nikki redecorates the theatre and releases Shankranna's film to the audience. He later reconciles with Shwetha, who agrees to marry him.\n\nIn the dream, Shankranna is kidnapped, and Nikhil rescues him with the help of the police. In the process, all of the goons are either arrested or killed except for the contract killer. Nikhil feels Shankranna is not safe with him and decides to fire him. Nikhil breaks up with Shwetha and sends off all his servants so as to be alone. Later, a visibly disturbed Nikhil finds himself in a thrashed room. Nikhil gets hold of a torch and through its light sees his life as a \"torch-shiner\" projected on the walls of the room.\n\nShwetha is now distraught with being in the limelight and understands what Nikhil had tried to tell her. Nikhil, the actor, meets Shwetha and tells her that he cannot decide if the present moment is a dream or reality but he is ultimately happy. Asking Shwetha to close her eyes, Nikhil jumps off the roof to the confusion of everyone present, including the contract killer waiting to kill him.\n\nAt present, Sanjay with the help of the suspects, performs a sting operation on the drug dealer and learns more about the Lucia pills. Meanwhile, Shwetha is caught in an attempt to kill Nikhil by pulling him off life support. During her interrogation, the whole investigating team along with Shwetha watches a re-run of an interview of the film star Nikhil. In the interview, Nikhil expresses his dissatisfaction of the stardom and reveals that he is actually color blind from an accident in his childhood. He tells the interviewer that he dreams of being a normal person and in fact in one of his dreams he is a \"torch-shiner\" who gets no attention from people and is happily in love with the dream of his life.\n \nSanjay is now convinced that Nikhil is living in his own version of reality and chose to live in that dream rather than in the real world by attempting suicide. Sanjay gets Shwetha to act and behave like she was in Nikhil's dream, and acts himself as if he was a contract killer and shoots the comatose Nikhil in the head with an empty gun. Simultaneously, Nikhil, aware and alive in his dream world finds everything disappearing around him and is killed by a shot to the head. Nikhi wakes up from his coma to see the astonished doctors and Shwetha's relieved face.\n\nAt the end we can see Nikhil, Swetha and Shankaranna (who was dead in Nikhil's dream) enjoying pizza (Swetha worked as pizza waitress in Nikhil's dream) while they operate the projector of an old theater. Thus revealing that it was film star Nikhil's dream to be a commoner like Nikki, and he achieved it through Lucid dreams.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sathish Ninasam]] as Nikki/Nikhil\n* [[Sruthi Hariharan]] as Shwetha\n* [[Achyuth Kumar]] as Shankranna\n* Sanjay as Sanjay (Mumbai police)\n*  Krishna as Deepak (Crime branch officer)\n* Balaji Manohar\n* Hardika Shetty as Kamini\n* Aaryan Achukatla as Aryan (second lead/model)\n* Ram Manjjonaath\n* Venky\n*[[Rishab Shetty]]\n\n==Production==\nIn December 2011 [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]] announced on the Web that his next project, after the success of his directorial debut film ''[[Lifeu Ishtene]]'', was going to be ''Lucia''. For the next two months, he met quite a few producers and top actors and found it difficult to fund his film. That led Pawan Kumar to write a post titled Making Enemies on his blog. Three days after it was published, the response was so overwhelming that he decided to pitch the idea of inviting people to produce the film and Pawan Kumar initiated Project Lucia.<ref>[http://postnoon.com/2013/05/26/swimming-against-thetide/127211 Swimming Against TheTide : Postnoon<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://pawantheactor.com/?page_id=1653 Project Lucia | Pawan Kumar<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Lucia is notable for its use of [[crowdfunding]]. It was funded by 110 investors who contributed to the project through a [[Facebook]] page and a blog run by director-actor Pawan Kumar. It was the first [[Kannada]] movie to bypass the traditional film financing model.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-03/mangalore/40350594_1_crowd-funding-pawan-kumar-yogaraj Gen Y film makers home in on crowd funding - Times Of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The director initially offered the lead role to model turned actor [[Diganth]] but he was later replaced by [[Sathish Ninasam]], who has played supporting roles in many Kannada films.<ref>[http://ibnlive.in.com/news/satish-replaces-diganth-in-kannada-film-lucia/259597-71-205.html Satish replaces Diganth in Kannada film 'Lucia'<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''Lucia'' was made at a budget of {{INRConvert|0.50|c}}.<ref name=\"th1\">{{cite web |author= Khajane, Muralidhara |title= Lucia goes to Pakistan |url= http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/lucia-goes-to-pakistan/article7118095.ece |work= The Hindu |publisher= thehindu.com |date= 19 April 2015 |accessdate= 19 April 2015}}</ref> Kannada language television channel [[Udaya TV]] bought the satellite rights of the film for {{INRConvert|0.95|c}}.<ref>[http://dearcinema.com/news/kannada-indie-lucia-grosses-56-lakhs-opening-weekend/0258 Kannada indie Lucia collects 56 lakhs in its opening weekend | DearCinema.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Actor Sathish Ninasam along with the music director Poornachandra Tejaswi visited colleges in Davangere to promote ''Lucia''.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-14/news-interviews/42061593_1_first-crowd-funded-movie-movie-lucia-shruti-hariharan Satish promotes Lucia in Davangere - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Lucia\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Poornachandra Tejaswi (composer)|Poornachandra Tejaswi]]\n| cover      = Lucia audio.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Soundtrack cover\n| released   = {{Start date|2013|06|10|df=yes}}\n| recorded   = 2012-13\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=27|s=40}}\n| label      = Anand Audio\n| producer   = Valerie\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nThe music for the film and soundtracks were composed by debutant Poornachandra Tejaswi, and background score composed by Poornachandra Tejaswi, Monish Kumar M.K. and [[Santhosh Narayanan]]. The lyrics were penned by Poornachandra Tejaswi, [[Yogaraj Bhat]] and Raghu Shastri.<ref>{{cite web |title= Lucia (2013) songs |url= http://play.raaga.com/kannada/album/lucia-K0001922 |website= raaga.com |accessdate= 21 August 2014}}</ref> The album has seven tracks.<ref>{{cite web |title= Lucia (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |url= https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/lucia-original-motion-picture/id657759898 |publisher= iTunes |date= |accessdate= 20 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| headline       = Track listing\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| total_length   =  27:40\n| title1         = Thinbedakami 1\n| extra1         = Poornachandra Tejaswi, Arun M. C., Bappi Blossom\n| music1         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics1        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length1        = 3:55\n| title2         = Nee Thoreda Galigeyali\n| extra2         = Udith Haritas, [[Ananya Bhat]]\n| music2         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics2        = Raghu Shastri\n| length2        = 4:19\n| title3         = Jamma Jamma\n| extra3         = Naveen Sajju\n| music3         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics3        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length3        = 4:13\n| title4         = Yako Barlilla\n| extra4         = Naveen Sajju\n| music4         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics4        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length4        = 4:13\n| title5         = Helu Shiva\n| extra5         = Naveen Sajju, [[Yogaraj Bhat]], Rakshith Nagarle\n| music5         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics5        = Yogaraj Bhat\n| length5        = 4:01\n| title6         = Jamma Jamma Patho\n| extra6         = Naveen Sajju\n| music6         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics6        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length6        = 3:03\n| title7         = Thinbedakami 2\n| extra7         = [[Sangeetha Rajeev]], Nithin Acharya, Sparsha R. K.\n| music7         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics7        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length7        = 3:56\n}}\n\n==Release==\nThe trailer of Lucia was released in February 2013, with the film releasing on 6 September 2013.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-08/news-interviews/36992090_1_kannada-film-industry-lucia-gadda-vijay Lucia trailer released - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> PVR released the film on 6 September 2013 under their \"Director\u2019s Rare\" category all over India. It was released across [[Bangalore]], [[Chennai]], [[Kochi]], [[Hyderabad]], [[Mumbai]], [[Pune]], [[Ahmedabad]], [[Surat]], and [[Delhi]] with English subtitles.<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-kannada-film-lucia-to-have-a-nationwide-release/20130826.htm Kannada film Lucia to have a nationwide release - Rediff.com Movies<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''Lucia'' was also set to be released in [[Pakistan]].<ref>[http://ibnlive.in.com/news/pawan-kumars-kannada-film-lucia-to-be-released-in-pakistan/426154-71-205.html Pawan Kumar's Kannada film 'Lucia' to be released in Pakistan - IBNLive<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-10-02/news-interviews/42614864_1_london-indian-film-festival-sathish-neenasam-lucia Lucia to be released in Pakistan? - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n<!--DO ''not'' ADD UNNOTABLE SITES LIKE IDLEBRAIN, GREATANDHRA , NOWRUNNING AND SUPERGOODMOVIES IN THE TABLE.-->\n| rev1 =[[Times of India]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/kannada/movie-reviews/Lucia/movie-review/22398095.cms Lucia movie review: Wallpaper, Story, Trailer at Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n| rev2 =Wogma\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>[http://wogma.com/movie/lucia-review/ Lucia - Review<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n| rev3 =[[Deccan Herald]]\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>[http://www.deccanherald.com/content/355771/it039s-all-mind.html It's all in the mind<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n||}}\nThe critics praised the film.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/kannada/news-interviews/Anurag-Kashyap-tweets-about-Lucia/articleshow/22413053.cms Anurag Kashyap tweets about Lucia - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Anurag Kashyap tweeted \"My birthday gift to myself would be lucia...\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ankash1009/status/377270748362326016 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060803/https://twitter.com/ankash1009/status/377270748362326016 |archivedate=21 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Actor [[Siddharth (actor)|Siddharth]] was \"blown away\" after watching the movie. He immediately called the director Pawan Kumar and praised him. ''Lucia'' was also in the race for India's official entry to the Oscars.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-16/news-interviews/42113195_1_oscar-entry-kannada-films-star Kannada films for the Oscars? - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nThe movie received positive reviews from critics. Well known critic Baradwaj Rangan remarked, \"An entertaining new Kannada film pushes the envelope even as it pays homage to the old way of doing things\".<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/stranger-than-fiction/article5208712.ece Stranger than fiction <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Bookmyshow website said it is a landmark film for Indian cinema.<ref>[http://in.bookmyshow.com/entertainment/lucia-film-review/25845 Lucia: Film Review<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Tribune praised the film story.<ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/609642/movie-review-lucia-a-pill-worth-a-debate/ Movie review: Lucia&nbsp;\u2013 a pill worth a debate&nbsp;\u2013 The Express Tribune<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The Hindu stated that ''Lucia'' is a new type of Kannada film.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/stranger-than-fiction/article5149845.ece Stranger than fiction - The Hindu<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/a-shift-in-alt-cinema/1180512/ A Shift in Alt Cinema - Indian Express<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Box office==\n''Lucia'' earned {{INRConvert|0.95|c}} in satellite rights and {{INRConvert|3.06|c}} in ticket sales through its entire run in cinemas, far surpassing its production budget of around {{INRConvert|0.50|c}}. ''Lucia'' was also released by PVR Pictures in some cinemas outside Karnataka, fetching around {{INRConvert|8|l}} from 13 screens in the first three days.\n\n==Awards==\n; [[Karnataka State Film Awards]] 2013\n* [[Karnataka State Film Award for Best Music Director|Best Music Director]]&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi\n\n;[[61st Filmfare Awards South]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Kannada|Best Director]]&nbsp;\u2014 [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Kannada|Best Supporting Actor]]&nbsp;\u2014 [[Achyuth Kumar]] \n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi&nbsp;\u2013 \"Thinbedakammi\"\n\n;[[London Indian Film Festival]] 2013\n* Audience Choice Award<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Regional/Kannada-film-Lucia-wins-at-London-Indian-Film-Festival/Article1-1100289.aspx Kannada film Lucia wins at London Indian Film Festival - Hindustan Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n;Karnataka International Music Awards\n* Best Background Score&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi, Monish Kumar M. K., Santhosh Narayanan\n\n; [[3rd South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n* Best Cinematographer&nbsp;\u2014 [[Siddhartha Nuni]] (Nominated)\n\n==Influences and cultural references==\nDirector [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]] admitted to having taken influence from [[Christopher Nolan]] and [[David Lynch]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Chasing new frontiers|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/chasing-new-frontiers/article5121242.ece|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> The dream and real sequences being shot in [[Black and white|monochrome]] and in color to differentiate between the two stories, like the [[Memento (film)|Memento]] and [[Open Your Eyes (1997 film)|Open Your Eyes]] to alternate between two plot-lines. The movie's relation with dream and reality and the interrelation between the two. There is also a scene where Nolan's movie [[Following (film)|Following]] is seen playing on a TV screen. [[Requiem for a Dream]] is also seen playing on a TV in the same scene which is also an influence as the movie deals with addiction.<ref>http://imdb.com/title/tt2358592/trivia</ref> Apart from the cinematic influences, the theme of dream and illusion is also shown as an influence of the poem Nee Mayeyolago by [[Kanaka Dasa]] which is quoted at the beginning of the movie. The poem is also partially contained in the lyrics of the song Nee Toreda Galigeyali in the soundtrack. Crowdfunding in Kannada movies was another phenomenon that Pawan kick-started. Since then young filmmakers have started to follow CrowdFunding as one of the source for producing their movies like Sushupti Dreams team.\n\n==Home media==\nThe film was released in Blu-ray, HD DVD, DVD 5.1, VCD Version From Anand Video Studio. It is the first Kannada film to be released in Blu-ray. The director, an advocate of alternative distribution strategies for indie filmmakers, was recently quoted as saying, \"It\u2019s time to set up your own virtual movie theaters on the World Wide Web which will be open 24\u00d77 across the globe.\"<ref>http://dearcinema.com/article/pawan-kumar/3143</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Open Your Eyes (1997 film)|''Open Your Eyes'' (1997 film)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2358592|Lucia}}\n\n{{Pawan Kumar}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian independent films]]\n[[Category:Crowdfunded films]]\n[[Category:Kannada films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian psychological thriller films]]\n[[Category:Films about dreams]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n[[Category:Indian avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:2010s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lucia<br />\u0cb2\u0cc2\u0cb8\u0cbf\u0caf\n| image          = Lucia kannada film poster1.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]]\n| producer       = Audience films<br />Home Talkies\n| writer         = Pawan Kumar\n| screenplay     = Pawan Kumar\n| starring       = [[Sathish Ninasam]]<br />[[Sruthi Hariharan]]<br />[[Achyuth Kumar]]<br />[[Rishab Shetty]]\n| music          = [[Poornachandra Tejaswi (composer)|Poornachandra Tejaswi]]<br />'''Background music:'''<br />Poornachandra Tejaswi<br />Monish Kumar M. K.<br />[[Santhosh Narayanan]]\n| cinematography = [[Siddhartha Nuni]]\n| studio         = Audience films\n| distributor    = Home Talkies\n| editing        = Sanath\u2013Suresh<br />Pawan Kumar\n| released       = {{Film date|2013|07|20|[[London Film Festival]]|2013|9|6|India|df=y}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref name=\"th1\" />\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|3.6|c}}\n}}\n\n'''''Lucia''''' is a 2013 Indian [[Kannada]]-language [[romantic]] [[psychological thriller]] film written, co-edited and directed by [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Crowd-funding show gains pace with Kannada movie Lucia, over 100 people invest through Facebook & blog |url= http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2013-04-13/news/38511296_1_kannada-film-industry-lifeu-ishtene-first-kannada-movie |newspaper= The Economic Times |date= 13 April 2013}}</ref> It stars [[Sathish Ninasam]] and [[Sruthi Hariharan]].''<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-12/news-and-interviews/35049155_1_double-role-kannada-flick Sruthi gets busy \u2013 The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>''\n\nThe film's plot is about Nikki, an usher in theatre who has insomnia. After consuming a special pill, he gets entangled in a different kind of dream. ''Lucia'' was the first Kannada film to be [[crowdfunded]] by the people which created a trend. The film's soundtrack was composed by Poornachandra Tejaswi and cinematography was handled by [[Siddhartha Nuni]].\n\n''Lucia'' premiered at the [[London Indian Film Festival]] on 20 July 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title= Lucia to premiere at LIFF |url= http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Lucia-to-premiere-at-LIFF/2013/07/02/article1662455.ece |newspaper= The Indian Express |date= 2 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Indian Film Festival 2013&nbsp;\u2013 London |url= http://www.britishsouthindians.co.uk/indian-film-festival-2013-london/ |publisher= britishsouthindians}}</ref> It won the Best Film Audience Choice award at the festival.<ref>{{cite news |title= Crowd-funded 'Lucia' wins smash hit 4th edition of LIFF |url= http://www.londonindianfilmfestival.co.uk/cgi-bin/template.pl?t=npd&ID=130 |publisher= London Indian Film Festival |access-date= 15 August 2013 |archive-url= https://archive.is/20130815032638/http://www.londonindianfilmfestival.co.uk/cgi-bin/template.pl?t=npd&ID=130 |archive-date= 15 August 2013 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\nIt was also among the films shortlisted by the FFI to become India's submission for Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film for the year 2013. The film was also remade in Tamil as ''[[Enakkul Oruvan (2015 film)|Enakkul Oruvan]]'' in 2015.\n\n==Plot==\n{{tone|section|date=August 2015}}\nThe plot is non-linear, and the end scene of the film shows the real beginning of the story.<ref name=fiction>{{cite news|title=Stranger than fiction|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/stranger-than-fiction/article5149845.ece|accessdate=4 November 2013|newspaper=TheHindu|date=20 September 2013}}</ref> There are two main roles, one that is played out in the dream, and the other one in reality, called respectively Nikhil and Nikki.<ref name=fiction/> The plot starts with the protagonist being in a state of coma and continuing only on life support. The film, from the beginning, tells two stories of the same person, one in colour and the other in black and white.<ref name=sarit>{{cite news|title=Sarit Ray's review: Lucia|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Sarit-Ray-s-review-Lucia/Article1-1119075.aspx|accessdate=4 November 2013|newspaper=The Hindustan Times|date=8 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nSanjay, a detective from the Mumbai police Crime Branch starts investigating the incident that caused the protagonist's ([[Sathish Ninasam]]) current state. While Sanjay is going through the protagonist's belongings he stumbles upon some scribbled notes and a mysterious pill. Meanwhile, the police capture two suspects and interrogate them.\n\nThe story starts with Nikki in a village near Mandya, working as an usher/\"torch-shiner\" in a Bengaluru movie theatre owned by Shankranna (Achyuth Kumar). Nikki has insomnia and yearns for a companion. On one of his sleepless nights Nikki is contacted by a drug dealer who gives him Lucia pills as a solution to his sleeping problems. This drug is said to have the capacity to help one dream the life they want, but has the side-effect that upon discontinuation the same dreams turn into nightmares.\n\nWith the help of the Lucia pills, Nikki starts seeing himself as being a successful actor called Nikhil surrounded by people he knows in the real world. Film actor Nikhil's life is depicted in black-and-white. Shankranna, the owner of the theater where Nikki works, had starred in a film in his youth funded by the leader of some goons who now want Shankranna to sign off his theatre for his debt. More events from the dream are followed by similar events in reality as Nikki falls in love with Shwetha ([[Sruthi Hariharan]]) who is a model in the dream and a waitress in reality.\n\nIn the dream, Nikhil and Shwetha hit it off easily at the beginning but later friction arises when Nikhil expresses his discontent about Shwetha working in the film industry. Meanwhile, in reality, Nikki struggles to win Shwetha's heart, who rejects him first due to his low salary but later falls for his humble character. Shwetha's attempts to get Nikki educated and lead him to find a better paying job turns out to be futile and also result in the death of Shankranna in the hands of goons. Frustrated, Nikki chooses to leave Shwetha and continue to work in the theatre, despite the threats. Nikki redecorates the theatre and releases Shankranna's film to the audience. He later reconciles with Shwetha, who agrees to marry him.\n\nIn the dream, Shankranna is kidnapped, and Nikhil rescues him with the help of the police. In the process, all of the goons are either arrested or killed except for the contract killer. Nikhil feels Shankranna is not safe with him and decides to fire him. Nikhil breaks up with Shwetha and sends off all his servants so as to be alone. Later, a visibly disturbed Nikhil finds himself in a thrashed room. Nikhil gets hold of a torch and through its light sees his life as a \"torch-shiner\" projected on the walls of the room.\n\nShwetha is now distraught with being in the limelight and understands what Nikhil had tried to tell her. Nikhil, the actor, meets Shwetha and tells her that he cannot decide if the present moment is a dream or reality but he is ultimately happy. Asking Shwetha to close her eyes, Nikhil jumps off the roof to the confusion of everyone present, including the contract killer waiting to kill him.\n\nAt present, Sanjay with the help of the suspects, performs a sting operation on the drug dealer and learns more about the Lucia pills. Meanwhile, Shwetha is caught in an attempt to kill Nikhil by pulling him off life support. During her interrogation, the whole investigating team along with Shwetha watches a re-run of an interview of the film star Nikhil. In the interview, Nikhil expresses his dissatisfaction of the stardom and reveals that he is actually color blind from an accident in his childhood. He tells the interviewer that he dreams of being a normal person and in fact in one of his dreams he is a \"torch-shiner\" who gets no attention from people and is happily in love with the dream of his life.\n \nSanjay is now convinced that Nikhil is living in his own version of reality and chose to live in that dream rather than in the real world by attempting suicide. Sanjay gets Shwetha to act and behave like she was in Nikhil's dream, and acts himself as if he was a contract killer and shoots the comatose Nikhil in the head with an empty gun. Simultaneously, Nikhil, aware and alive in his dream world finds everything disappearing around him and is killed by a shot to the head. Nikhi wakes up from his coma to see the astonished doctors and Shwetha's relieved face.\n\nAt the end we can see Nikhil, Swetha and Shankaranna (who was dead in Nikhil's dream) enjoying pizza (Swetha worked as pizza waitress in Nikhil's dream) while they operate the projector of an old theater. Thus revealing that it was film star Nikhil's dream to be a commoner like Nikki, and he achieved it through Lucid dreams.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sathish Ninasam]] as Nikki/Nikhil\n* [[Sruthi Hariharan]] as Shwetha\n* [[Achyuth Kumar]] as Shankranna\n* Sanjay as Sanjay (Mumbai police)\n*  Krishna as Deepak (Crime branch officer)\n* Balaji Manohar\n* Hardika Shetty as Kamini\n* Aaryan Achukatla as Aryan (second lead/model)\n* Ram Manjjonaath\n* Venky\n*[[Rishab Shetty]]\n\n==Production==\nIn December 2011 [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]] announced on the Web that his next project, after the success of his directorial debut film ''[[Lifeu Ishtene]]'', was going to be ''Lucia''. For the next two months, he met quite a few producers and top actors and found it difficult to fund his film. That led Pawan Kumar to write a post titled Making Enemies on his blog. Three days after it was published, the response was so overwhelming that he decided to pitch the idea of inviting people to produce the film and Pawan Kumar initiated Project Lucia.<ref>[http://postnoon.com/2013/05/26/swimming-against-thetide/127211 Swimming Against TheTide : Postnoon<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://pawantheactor.com/?page_id=1653 Project Lucia | Pawan Kumar<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Lucia is notable for its use of [[crowdfunding]]. It was funded by 110 investors who contributed to the project through a [[Facebook]] page and a blog run by director-actor Pawan Kumar. It was the first [[Kannada]] movie to bypass the traditional film financing model.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-03/mangalore/40350594_1_crowd-funding-pawan-kumar-yogaraj Gen Y film makers home in on crowd funding - Times Of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The director initially offered the lead role to model turned actor [[Diganth]] but he was later replaced by [[Sathish Ninasam]], who has played supporting roles in many Kannada films.<ref>[http://ibnlive.in.com/news/satish-replaces-diganth-in-kannada-film-lucia/259597-71-205.html Satish replaces Diganth in Kannada film 'Lucia'<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''Lucia'' was made at a budget of {{INRConvert|0.50|c}}.<ref name=\"th1\">{{cite web |author= Khajane, Muralidhara |title= Lucia goes to Pakistan |url= http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/lucia-goes-to-pakistan/article7118095.ece |work= The Hindu |publisher= thehindu.com |date= 19 April 2015 |accessdate= 19 April 2015}}</ref> Kannada language television channel [[Udaya TV]] bought the satellite rights of the film for {{INRConvert|0.95|c}}.<ref>[http://dearcinema.com/news/kannada-indie-lucia-grosses-56-lakhs-opening-weekend/0258 Kannada indie Lucia collects 56 lakhs in its opening weekend | DearCinema.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Actor Sathish Ninasam along with the music director Poornachandra Tejaswi visited colleges in Davangere to promote ''Lucia''.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-14/news-interviews/42061593_1_first-crowd-funded-movie-movie-lucia-shruti-hariharan Satish promotes Lucia in Davangere - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Lucia\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Poornachandra Tejaswi (composer)|Poornachandra Tejaswi]]\n| cover      = Lucia audio.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Soundtrack cover\n| released   = {{Start date|2013|06|10|df=yes}}\n| recorded   = 2012-13\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=27|s=40}}\n| label      = Anand Audio\n| producer   = Valerie\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nThe music for the film and soundtracks were composed by debutant Poornachandra Tejaswi, and background score composed by Poornachandra Tejaswi, Monish Kumar M.K. and [[Santhosh Narayanan]]. The lyrics were penned by Poornachandra Tejaswi, [[Yogaraj Bhat]] and Raghu Shastri.<ref>{{cite web |title= Lucia (2013) songs |url= http://play.raaga.com/kannada/album/lucia-K0001922 |website= raaga.com |accessdate= 21 August 2014}}</ref> The album has seven tracks.<ref>{{cite web |title= Lucia (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |url= https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/lucia-original-motion-picture/id657759898 |publisher= iTunes |date= |accessdate= 20 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| headline       = Track listing\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| total_length   =  27:40\n| title1         = Thinbedakami 1\n| extra1         = Poornachandra Tejaswi, Arun M. C., Bappi Blossom\n| music1         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics1        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length1        = 3:55\n| title2         = Nee Thoreda Galigeyali\n| extra2         = Udith Haritas, [[Ananya Bhat]]\n| music2         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics2        = Raghu Shastri\n| length2        = 4:19\n| title3         = Jamma Jamma\n| extra3         = Naveen Sajju\n| music3         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics3        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length3        = 4:13\n| title4         = Yako Barlilla\n| extra4         = Naveen Sajju\n| music4         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics4        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length4        = 4:13\n| title5         = Helu Shiva\n| extra5         = Naveen Sajju, [[Yogaraj Bhat]], Rakshith Nagarle\n| music5         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics5        = Yogaraj Bhat\n| length5        = 4:01\n| title6         = Jamma Jamma Patho\n| extra6         = Naveen Sajju\n| music6         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics6        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length6        = 3:03\n| title7         = Thinbedakami 2\n| extra7         = [[Sangeetha Rajeev]], Nithin Acharya, Sparsha R. K.\n| music7         = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| lyrics7        = Poornachandra Tejaswi\n| length7        = 3:56\n}}\n\n==Release==\nThe trailer of Lucia was released in February 2013, with the film releasing on 6 September 2013.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-08/news-interviews/36992090_1_kannada-film-industry-lucia-gadda-vijay Lucia trailer released - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> PVR released the film on 6 September 2013 under their \"Director\u2019s Rare\" category all over India. It was released across [[Bangalore]], [[Chennai]], [[Kochi]], [[Hyderabad]], [[Mumbai]], [[Pune]], [[Ahmedabad]], [[Surat]], and [[Delhi]] with English subtitles.<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-kannada-film-lucia-to-have-a-nationwide-release/20130826.htm Kannada film Lucia to have a nationwide release - Rediff.com Movies<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''Lucia'' was also set to be released in [[Pakistan]].<ref>[http://ibnlive.in.com/news/pawan-kumars-kannada-film-lucia-to-be-released-in-pakistan/426154-71-205.html Pawan Kumar's Kannada film 'Lucia' to be released in Pakistan - IBNLive<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-10-02/news-interviews/42614864_1_london-indian-film-festival-sathish-neenasam-lucia Lucia to be released in Pakistan? - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n<!--DO ''not'' ADD UNNOTABLE SITES LIKE IDLEBRAIN, GREATANDHRA , NOWRUNNING AND SUPERGOODMOVIES IN THE TABLE.-->\n| rev1 =[[Times of India]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/kannada/movie-reviews/Lucia/movie-review/22398095.cms Lucia movie review: Wallpaper, Story, Trailer at Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n| rev2 =Wogma\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>[http://wogma.com/movie/lucia-review/ Lucia - Review<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n| rev3 =[[Deccan Herald]]\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>[http://www.deccanherald.com/content/355771/it039s-all-mind.html It's all in the mind<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n||}}\nThe critics praised the film.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/kannada/news-interviews/Anurag-Kashyap-tweets-about-Lucia/articleshow/22413053.cms Anurag Kashyap tweets about Lucia - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Anurag Kashyap tweeted \"My birthday gift to myself would be lucia...\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ankash1009/status/377270748362326016 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060803/https://twitter.com/ankash1009/status/377270748362326016 |archivedate=21 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Actor [[Siddharth (actor)|Siddharth]] was \"blown away\" after watching the movie. He immediately called the director Pawan Kumar and praised him. ''Lucia'' was also in the race for India's official entry to the Oscars.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-16/news-interviews/42113195_1_oscar-entry-kannada-films-star Kannada films for the Oscars? - The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nThe movie received positive reviews from critics. Well known critic Baradwaj Rangan remarked, \"An entertaining new Kannada film pushes the envelope even as it pays homage to the old way of doing things\".<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/stranger-than-fiction/article5208712.ece Stranger than fiction <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Bookmyshow website said it is a landmark film for Indian cinema.<ref>[http://in.bookmyshow.com/entertainment/lucia-film-review/25845 Lucia: Film Review<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Tribune praised the film story.<ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/609642/movie-review-lucia-a-pill-worth-a-debate/ Movie review: Lucia&nbsp;\u2013 a pill worth a debate&nbsp;\u2013 The Express Tribune<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The Hindu stated that ''Lucia'' is a new type of Kannada film.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/stranger-than-fiction/article5149845.ece Stranger than fiction - The Hindu<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/a-shift-in-alt-cinema/1180512/ A Shift in Alt Cinema - Indian Express<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Box office==\n''Lucia'' earned {{INRConvert|0.95|c}} in satellite rights and {{INRConvert|3.06|c}} in ticket sales through its entire run in cinemas, far surpassing its production budget of around {{INRConvert|0.50|c}}. ''Lucia'' was also released by PVR Pictures in some cinemas outside Karnataka, fetching around {{INRConvert|8|l}} from 13 screens in the first three days.\n\n==Awards==\n; [[Karnataka State Film Awards]] 2013\n* [[Karnataka State Film Award for Best Music Director|Best Music Director]]&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi\n\n;[[61st Filmfare Awards South]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Kannada|Best Director]]&nbsp;\u2014 [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Kannada|Best Supporting Actor]]&nbsp;\u2014 [[Achyuth Kumar]] \n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi&nbsp;\u2013 \"Thinbedakammi\"\n\n;[[London Indian Film Festival]] 2013\n* Audience Choice Award<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Regional/Kannada-film-Lucia-wins-at-London-Indian-Film-Festival/Article1-1100289.aspx Kannada film Lucia wins at London Indian Film Festival - Hindustan Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n;Karnataka International Music Awards\n* Best Background Score&nbsp;\u2014 Poornachandra Tejaswi, Monish Kumar M. K., Santhosh Narayanan\n\n; [[3rd South Indian International Movie Awards]]\n* Best Cinematographer&nbsp;\u2014 [[Siddhartha Nuni]] (Nominated)\n\n==Influences and cultural references==\nDirector [[Pawan Kumar (director)|Pawan Kumar]] admitted to have taken influence from [[Christopher Nolan]] and [[David Lynch]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Chasing new frontiers|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/chasing-new-frontiers/article5121242.ece|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> The dream and real sequences being shot in [[Black and white|monochrome]] and in color to differentiate between the two stories, like the [[Memento (film)|Memento]] and [[Open Your Eyes (1997 film)|Open Your Eyes]] to alternate between two plot-lines. The movie's relation with dream and reality and the interrelation between the two. There is also a scene where Nolan's movie [[Following (film)|Following]] is seen playing on a TV screen. [[Requiem for a Dream]] is also seen playing on a TV in the same scene which is also an influence as the movie deals with addiction.<ref>http://imdb.com/title/tt2358592/trivia</ref> Apart from the cinematic influences, the theme of dream and illusion is also shown as an influence of the poem Nee Mayeyolago by [[Kanaka Dasa]] which is quoted at the beginning of the movie. The poem is also partially contained in the lyrics of the song Nee Toreda Galigeyali in the soundtrack.\n\n==Home media==\nThe film was released in Blu-ray, HD DVD, DVD 5.1, VCD Version From Anand Video Studio. It is the first Kannada film to be released in Blu-ray. The director, an advocate of alternative distribution strategies for indie filmmakers, was recently quoted as saying, \"It\u2019s time to set up your own virtual movie theaters on the World Wide Web which will be open 24\u00d77 across the globe.\"<ref>http://dearcinema.com/article/pawan-kumar/3143</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Open Your Eyes (1997 film)|''Open Your Eyes'' (1997 film)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2358592|Lucia}}\n\n{{Pawan Kumar}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian independent films]]\n[[Category:Crowdfunded films]]\n[[Category:Kannada films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian psychological thriller films]]\n[[Category:Films about dreams]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n[[Category:Indian avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:2010s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n", "name_user": "ManjuSomashekar", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eInfluences and cultural references)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucia_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Philippe Ghanem", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n<br />{{Infobox person\n| name        = Philippe Ghanem\n| image       = Philippe Ghanem.jpg\n| alt         =\n| caption     =\n| birth_name  = <!--only use if different from name-->\n| birth_date  = {{Birth-date and age|October 4, 1980}}\n| birth_place = [[Switzerland]]\n| residence = [[Geneva]] and [[Abu Dhabi]]<ref>{{cite news | title =Volatility Boosts Forex Trading Investment | author =Aarti Nagraj | url =http://gulfbusiness.com/2014/04/volatility-boosts-forex-trading-investment/#.U2ESL61dW2B | date =April 20, 2014 | accessdate =May 1, 2014 }}</ref>\n| relatives = {{sibling|[[Sabine Getty]]}}\n| death_date  = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| alma_mater = [[International University in Geneva]], 2002\n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| occupation  = \n| known_for   = {{unbulleted list |Executive Chairman at SquaredFinancial<ref>{{cite magazine | title = SquaredFinancial Managament Team | url = https://squaredfinancial.com/about/our-team | accessdate = April 13, 2020 }}</ref>|CEO ADS Securities|Vice chairman of ADS Holding<ref>{{cite magazine | title = \u0642\u064a\u0645\u0629\u064c \u0645\u0636\u0627\u0641\u0629\u064c | url = http://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/said.php?id=200 | magazine = Forbes | accessdate = May 1, 2014 }}</ref>|Chairman of ADS Securities London Limited}}\n}}\n\n'''Philippe Ghanem''' (born 4 October 1980), a Swiss and Emirati national, is a \u2018C\u2019 suite executive who is seen as an innovator and visionary in global financial markets. As an investor, and an expert in trading a range of asset classes, he has developed a reputation for building financial services companies based on his insight and understanding of trading systems. He and how these are driven by changes in market conditions, regulation and technology.\n\nWell defined people management skills gained from 15 years of senior leadership and high-level management roles, with responsibility for over 300 employees across multiple international regulatory environments. He has a track record of building and maintaining the performance of teams to achieve financial and commercial goals. He has developed and launched a number of retail and institutional trading firms including the Abu Dhabi based ADSS Group, where he was CEO and vice-chairman.  It was announced on 25 June 2019 [https://www.reuters.com/article/emirates-adss-moves/moves-ceo-of-abu-dhabis-adss-to-leave-brokerage-idUSD5N22E02Z 27] [https://www.ft.com/content/f5f9ff74-9647-11e9-8cfb-30c211dcd229 28] that at the start of the year he had expressed his desire to leave the organisation to pursue the development of a new entrepreneurial project.\n\n==Career==\n\nIn 2005, Philippe Ghanem and Georges Cohen co-founded the Dublin-based Squared Financial Services Limited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfinance.com/home/news/fx-platforms-target-white-labelling|title=FX platforms target white labelling|publisher=World Finance|date=5 January 2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #13 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbesasiaconferences.com/forbesglobalceoconference2011/speakers.php|title=Speakers|publisher=Forbes Global CEO Conference|date=2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #14 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> In February 2011, Ghanem was appointed managing director of ADS Securities. The firm rebranded to ADSS in June 2018. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.leaprate.com/forex/brokers/ads-securities-rebrands-adss-new-website/|title= ADS Securities rebrands as ADSS, new website adss.com |publisher= Leaprate|date=27 June 2018|accessdate=29 June 2018}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #15 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/markets/abu-dhabi-based-broker-soars-to-2bn-daily-trading|title=Abu Dhabi-based broker soars to $2bn daily trading|author=Bradley Hope|publisher=The National|date=23 February 2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #16 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> when he held the roles of CEO of ADSS and vice chairman of ADSS Group, ADSS' parent company.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://al-sayad.com/article.php?articleID=10425 | title = \u0645\u0644\u062d\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u064a\u0627\u062f | publisher = AL Sayad | accessdate = 10 March 2015 | language = Arabic}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #17 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.alidarimagazine.com/article.php?categoryID=46&articleID=1909 | title = \u0645\u0644\u0641 \u062e\u0627 | publisher = Al Idari Magazine | accessdate = 10 March 2015 | language = Arabic}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #18 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref>.  His departure from ADSS was announced on 25 June 2019. [https://www.reuters.com/article/emirates-adss-moves/moves-ceo-of-abu-dhabis-adss-to-leave-brokerage-idUSD5N22E02Z 27] [https://www.ft.com/content/f5f9ff74-9647-11e9-8cfb-30c211dcd229 28]\n\nIn 2020, Philippe Ghanem returns back to SquaredFinancial <ref>{{cite magazine | title = SquaredFinancial Managament Team | url = https://squaredfinancial.com/about/our-team | accessdate = April 13, 2020 }}</ref> to take the company through the next stage of its development <ref>{{cite magazine | title = Philippe Ghanem Becomes Executive Chairman at SquaredFinancial | url = https://www.financemagnates.com/executives/moves/former-adss-ceo-philippe-ghanem-becomes-executive-chairman-at-squaredfinancial/ | accessdate = April 13, 2020 }}</ref>.\n\nGhanem was a featured speaker at the [[Forbes]] Global CEO Conference, held in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]], in September 2011 and at London's Abu Dhabi Investment Forum in October 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbesasiaconferences.com/forbesglobalceoconference2011/speakers.php|title=Speakers|publisher=Forbes Global CEO Conference|date=2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #14 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxfordbusinessgroup.com/content/abu-dhabi-investment-forum-0|title=Abu Dhabi Investment Forum|publisher=Oxford Business Group|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #19 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/forbesasia/docs/pictorial11|title=Global CEOs gather at the crossroads|publisher=Forbes Global CEO Conference|date=2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #20 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> He is a regular contributor to international business media including as a guest host on CNBC Europe's Squawk Box program.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/50039256|title=Investors Cashing in on Middle East Forex Trade|author=Yousef Gamal El-Din|publisher=CNBC|date=1 December 2012|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #21 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> Ghanem was profiled by [[The Banker|The Banker Middle East]], an international financial news magazine, in November 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cpifinancial.net/flipbooks/BME/2016/189/files/assets/basic-html/index.html#1 | title = Conquering GCC and the world November | publisher = CPI Financial | date = November 2016}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #22 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref>\n\nHe is known for his expertise in managing the development of low latency multi-asset trading platforms, using [[Artificial Intelligence]] (AI) systems to increase returns and implementing [[blockchain]] technology as a way of developing new trading models.  He is also known for the introduction of blockchain trading systems and cryptocurrency into the GCC region.  His approach has been covered on [[CNBC]]. <ref>{{ cite web | url = https://www.cnbc.com/video/2017/10/17/bitcoin-will-be-the-future-securities-expert-says.html?play=1 | title = Bitcoin \u2018will be the future,\u2019 securities expert says | publisher = CNBC | date = 17 Oct 2017 | accessdate = 11 June 2018 }} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #23 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/16/siemens-is-expanding-in-the-middle-east-with-a-500-million-investment.html|title=Siemens is expanding in the Middle East with a $500 million internet of things investment|author= Natasha Turak |publisher=CNBC|date=16 April 2018|accessdate=11 June 2018}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #24 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nGhanem received his [[Bachelor of Science]] in [[business administration]] from the [[International University in Geneva]] in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://online.thomsonreuters.com/eDM/Email.aspx?id=ft634545375297347224e&version=1|title=Opportunities and challenges in Abu Dhabi the investment outlook and changing Middle East|work=Reuters|accessdate=8 April 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409101800/http://online.thomsonreuters.com/eDM/Email.aspx?id=ft634545375297347224e&version=1|archivedate=9 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #25 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> Ghanem was born in [[Switzerland]] and lives in Geneva.  On 20 June the Monaco Sport Academy announced a new collaboration with the Yacht Club de Monaco.  The initiative is presided over by Prince Albert II of Monaco, its general secretary Bernard d'Alessandri and Philippe Ghanem.[https://sfrpresse.sfr.fr/article/617e970a-daa1-4555-9ef8-f2058193d35b 29]  Mr Ghanem is fluent in English, French and Arabic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fx-mm.com/13071/fx-mm-magazine/past-issues/march-2012/ads-securities-making-waves/|title=ADS Securities: Making Waves|author=Steve Shaw|publisher=FX-MM|date=9 March 2012|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #26 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*[http://www.palfx.info/AR/portal/international/10563.html Philippe Ghanem talking about the Middle Eastern perspective]\n*[http://www.financemagnates.com/executives/interview/ads-securities-philippe-ghanem-talks-middle-eastern-fx-prospects/ Finance Magnates Philippe Ghanem interview]\n* [http://www.thebusinessyear.com/vip_interview/3450/philippe-ghanem VIP Interview Philippe Ghanem]\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ghanem, Philippe}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Swiss busines