ned from 15 years of senior leadership and high-level management roles, with responsibility for over 300 employees across multiple international regulatory environments. He has a track record of building and maintaining the performance of teams to achieve financial and commercial goals. He has developed and launched a number of retail and institutional trading firms including the Abu Dhabi based ADSS Group, where he was CEO and vice-chairman.  It was announced on 25 June 2019 [https://www.reuters.com/article/emirates-adss-moves/moves-ceo-of-abu-dhabis-adss-to-leave-brokerage-idUSD5N22E02Z 27] [https://www.ft.com/content/f5f9ff74-9647-11e9-8cfb-30c211dcd229 28] that at the start of the year he had expressed his desire to leave the organisation to pursue the development of a new entrepreneurial project.\n\n==Career==\n\nIn 2005, Philippe Ghanem and Georges Cohen co-founded the Dublin-based Squared Financial Services Limited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfinance.com/home/news/fx-platforms-target-white-labelling|title=FX platforms target white labelling|publisher=World Finance|date=5 January 2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #13 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbesasiaconferences.com/forbesglobalceoconference2011/speakers.php|title=Speakers|publisher=Forbes Global CEO Conference|date=2011|accessdate=8 April 2014}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904469872 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/903797819 cite #14 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC_bot/Job_18]]}}</ref> In February 2011, Ghanem was appointed managing director of A